  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow"><img src="/media/13052370/inghams_agency-sales_with_globe-travel-award.jpg" alt="Inghams Agents Team" rel="486,486" /></div>
<!-- <div style="height: 15px; font-size: x-small;">L-R: Andy Perrin (CEO, Hotelplan UK), Ashley Toft (MD, Explore Worldwide) &amp; Andrew Stewart (CFO, Hotelplan UK).</div> -->
<div> </div>
<p>On 14th Jan at a glittering ceremony at London's Grosvenor House Hotel, <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk">Inghams</a> was crowned <strong>Best Activity and Adventure Operator 2016</strong>, as voted for by UK travel agents.</p>
<p>The competition was stiff, in one of the biggest categories of the night.</p>
<p>Full list of nominees in this category:</p>
<p>Club Med<br />Crystal Ski<br />Exodus<br />Explore<br />G Adventures<br />Inghams<br />Intrepid Travel<br />Mark Warner<br />Neilson</p>
<p><br />The <strong>Golden Globe Trophy</strong> will be on display at Inghams HQ from today.</p>
<p>More pictures from the evening can be found using hashtag <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/twglobes" target="_blank">#twglobes</a></p>
<p><strong>Louise Newton, Head of Marketing said</strong>: "<em>It was a huge privilege to receive this award, on behalf of everyone at Inghams, both in the UK and in resort. It means a lot that our efforts have been rewarded. I believe it is our personal touch that makes the difference: we care immensely about our guests, and go the extra mile throughout the seasons to ensure we meet expectations."</em></p>
<p>ENDS. </p>
<p>For bookings please visit <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk">www.inghams.co.uk</a> or call 01483 791 114. </p>
<p>For PR enquiries please contact Rachel Gaston, PR Executive, <a href="mailto:rachel.gaston@inghams.co.uk">rachel.gaston@inghams.co.uk</a> or call 01483 791 045. </p>
<p><em> </em></p>
